The paper deals with distributed computing and graph algorithms, which are typically categorized under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper specifically focuses on local algorithms, which are a subset of distributed algorithms that operate on a small neighborhood of each node in the network. This makes cs.AL (Algorithms) another likely sub-category. The paper also mentions the coloring problem, which falls under cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Overall, cs.DC and cs.DS are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.AL, cs.NI, and cs.SI.
